Pehlwan Goth (Urdu:   ) is one of the neighborhoods of Gulshan Town in Karachi, Sindh, Pakistan[1]. There are several ethnic groups in Pehlwan Goth including Sindhis as majority, Muhajirs, Punjabis,, Kashmiris, Seraikis, Pakhtuns, Balochis, etc. Over 95% of the population is Muslim; among other religious believers, Christians comprise around 5% of the total population. The population of Gulshan Town is estimated to be nearly one million. http://wikimapia.org/#lat=24.910824&lon=67.1420002&z=16&l=0&m=b 
